Name: acute gonococcal epididymo-orchitis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the lymphatics and subcutaneous tissue by nematodes of the superfamily Filarioidea.

Name: obsolete Haemophilus influenzae meningitis
Definition: A parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the lymphatics and subcutaneous tissue by nematodes of the superfamily Filarioidea.
